parameters.name: CreateTimeRange
parameters.description: The time range during which the spatiotemporal clusters were generated.

parameters.name: DatasetName
parameters.description: The name of the dataset. For information about how to create a dataset, see [CreateDataset](~~478160~~).

parameters.name: LocationDateClusterEndTimeRange
parameters.description: The time range during which the latest photo in a cluster was taken.

parameters.name: LocationDateClusterLevels
parameters.description: The container for the administrative division level of the spatiotemporal clusters to be queried.

parameters.name: LocationDateClusterStartTimeRange
parameters.description: The time range during which the earliest photo in a cluster was taken.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The number of entries per page. Valid values: \[1,100]. Default value: 20.

parameters.name: ObjectId
parameters.description: The ID of the cluster that you want to query. Specify this parameter if you want to query a specific spatiotemporal cluster. Otherwise, leave this parameter empty to query spatiotemporal clusters that meet the specified conditions.

parameters.name: Order
parameters.description:
The order that you use to sort the query results.

Valid values:

*   asc: ascending order. This is the default value.
*   desc: descending order.

parameters.name: ProjectName
parameters.description: The name of the project. You can obtain the name of the project from the response of the [CreateProject](~~478153~~) operation.

parameters.name: Sort
parameters.description:
The field that you use to sort the query results.

Valid values:

*   LocationDateClusterEndTime: by the time at which the latest photo in a cluster was taken.
*   CreateTime: by the creation time of a spatiotemporal cluster.
*   UpdateTime: by the update time of a spatiotemporal cluster.
*   LocationDateClusterStartTime: by the time at which the earliest photo in a cluster was taken. This is the default value.

parameters.name: Title
parameters.description: The characters that are included in the titles of spatiotemporal clusters to be queried. Matches are found by using fuzzy matching.

parameters.name: UpdateTimeRange
parameters.description: The time range during which the spatiotemporal clusters were updated.
